article.description: UC Riverside edges Cal State Northridge 66-62
article.headline: UC Riverside edges Cal State Northridge 66-62
article.linkText: UC Riverside edges Cal State Northridge 66-62
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. -- Taylor Johns scored 27 points, hitting all 13 of his shots from the free throw line, to lift UC Riverside to a 66-62 win over Cal State Northridge on Saturday. Jaylen Bland added 10 points, while Steven Thornton and Austin Quick had nine apiece for Riverside (10-11, 3-4 Big West), which shot just 19 of 52 from the field (36.5 percent) but held a 24-8 advantage in made free throws. Riverside trailed by 11 midway through the first half after Taelin Webb's 3-pointer gave Northridge (6-17, 2-6) a 20-9 lead. Steven Thornton hit a 3 at the other end to ignite a 17-4 run to give the Highlanders their first lead of the game. In the second half, Riverside took the lead for good with Alexander Larson's jumper with 10:45 left to make it 46-45 and the Highlanders hung on down the stretch. Landon Drew led Northridge with 16 points.
